#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an7.70"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an7.70:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 7 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 7 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an7.70:0.2"
msgid "7. Mahāvagga "
msgstr "7. The Great Chapter "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 70. Sakkaccasutta → sakkāragarukārasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an7.70:0.3"
msgid "70. Sakkaccasutta "
msgstr "70. Honor "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an7.70:1.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmato sāriputtassa rahogatassa paṭisallīnassa evaṃ cetaso parivitakko udapādi: "
msgstr "Then as Venerable Sāriputta was in private retreat this thought came to his mind, "

# NOTE: Throughout this sutta, text punctuates as if bhikkhu was a vocative, sariputta talking to himself. However compare AN 4.21, where it is the nominative, as translated by BB.
msgctxt "an7.70:1.2"
msgid "“kiṃ nu kho, bhikkhu, sakkatvā garuṃ katvā upanissāya viharanto akusalaṃ pajaheyya, kusalaṃ bhāveyyā”ti? "
msgstr "“What should a mendicant honor and respect and rely on, to give up the unskillful and develop the skillful?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an7.70:1.3"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmato sāriputtassa etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then he thought, "

msgctxt "an7.70:1.4"
msgid "“satthāraṃ kho, bhikkhu, sakkatvā garuṃ katvā upanissāya viharanto akusalaṃ pajaheyya, kusalaṃ bhāveyya. "
msgstr "“A mendicant should honor and respect and rely on the Teacher … "

msgctxt "an7.70:1.5"
msgid "Dhammaṃ kho, bhikkhu … pe … "
msgstr "the teaching … "

msgctxt "an7.70:1.6"
msgid "saṃghaṃ kho, bhikkhu … pe … "
msgstr "the Saṅgha … "

msgctxt "an7.70:1.7"
msgid "sikkhaṃ kho, bhikkhu … pe … "
msgstr "the training … "

msgctxt "an7.70:1.8"
msgid "samādhiṃ kho, bhikkhu … pe … "
msgstr "immersion … "

msgctxt "an7.70:1.9"
msgid "appamādaṃ kho, bhikkhu … pe … "
msgstr "diligence … "

msgctxt "an7.70:1.10"
msgid "paṭisanthāraṃ kho, bhikkhu sakkatvā garuṃ katvā upanissāya viharanto akusalaṃ pajaheyya, kusalaṃ bhāveyyā”ti. "
msgstr "A mendicant should honor and respect and rely on hospitality, to give up the unskillful and develop the skillful.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an7.70:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmato sāriputtassa etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then he thought, "

#. VAR: gantvā → gahetvā (mr)
msgctxt "an7.70:2.2"
msgid "“ime kho me dhammā parisuddhā pariyodātā, yannūnāhaṃ ime dhamme gantvā bhagavato āroceyyaṃ. "
msgstr "“These qualities are pure and bright in me. Why don’t I go and tell them to the Buddha? "

msgctxt "an7.70:2.3"
msgid "Evaṃ me ime dhammā parisuddhā ceva bhavissanti parisuddhasaṅkhātatarā ca. "
msgstr "Then these qualities will not only be purified in me, but will be better known as purified. "

# NOTE: I don’t think BB’s “nugget” for nikkha is correct.
msgctxt "an7.70:2.4"
msgid "Seyyathāpi nāma puriso suvaṇṇanikkhaṃ adhigaccheyya parisuddhaṃ pariyodātaṃ. "
msgstr "Suppose a man were to acquire a gold ornament, pure and bright. "

msgctxt "an7.70:2.5"
msgid "Tassa evamassa: "
msgstr "They’d think, "

#. VAR: gantvā → gahetvā (mr)
msgctxt "an7.70:2.6"
msgid "‘ayaṃ kho me suvaṇṇanikkho parisuddho pariyodāto, yannūnāhaṃ imaṃ suvaṇṇanikkhaṃ gantvā kammārānaṃ dasseyyaṃ. "
msgstr "‘My gold ornament is pure and bright. Why don’t I take it to show the smiths? "

msgctxt "an7.70:2.7"
msgid "Evaṃ me ayaṃ suvaṇṇanikkho sakammāragato parisuddho ceva bhavissati parisuddhasaṅkhātataro ca. "
msgstr "Then it will not only be purified, but will be better known as purified.’ "

#. VAR: Evamevaṃ me → evamme (bj) | evameva evaṃ me (s1-3) | evaṃ me (pts1) | evamevaṃ kho me (mr)
#. VAR: gantvā → gahetvā (mr)
msgctxt "an7.70:2.8"
msgid "Evamevaṃ me ime dhammā parisuddhā pariyodātā, yannūnāhaṃ ime dhamme gantvā bhagavato āroceyyaṃ. "
msgstr "In the same way, these qualities are pure and bright in me. Why don’t I go and tell them to the Buddha? "

msgctxt "an7.70:2.9"
msgid "Evaṃ me ime dhammā parisuddhā ceva bhavissanti parisuddhasaṅkhātatarā cā’”ti. "
msgstr "Then these qualities will not only be purified in me, but will be better known as purified.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.121, sc3
msgctxt "an7.70:3.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā sāriputto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then in the late afternoon, Sāriputta came out of retreat and went to the Buddha. He bowed, sat down to one side, and told the Buddha of his thoughts while on retreat. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.122, sc4
msgctxt "an7.70:4.1"
msgid "“Idha mayhaṃ, bhante, rahogatassa paṭisallīnassa evaṃ cetaso parivitakko udapādi: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an7.70:4.2"
msgid "‘kiṃ nu kho bhikkhu sakkatvā garuṃ katvā upanissāya viharanto akusalaṃ pajaheyya, kusalaṃ bhāveyyā’ti? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an7.70:4.3"
msgid "Atha kho tassa mayhaṃ, bhante, etadahosi: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an7.70:4.4"
msgid "‘satthāraṃ kho bhikkhu sakkatvā garuṃ katvā upanissāya viharanto akusalaṃ pajaheyya, kusalaṃ bhāveyya. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an7.70:4.5"
msgid "Dhammaṃ kho bhikkhu … pe … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an7.70:4.6"
msgid "paṭisanthāraṃ kho bhikkhu sakkatvā … pe … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an7.70:4.7"
msgid "kusalaṃ bhāveyyā’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an7.70:4.8"
msgid "Atha kho tassa mayhaṃ, bhante, etadahosi: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an7.70:4.9"
msgid "‘ime kho me dhammā parisuddhā pariyodātā, yannūnāhaṃ ime dhamme gantvā bhagavato āroceyyaṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an7.70:4.10"
msgid "Evaṃ me ime dhammā parisuddhā ceva bhavissanti parisuddhasaṅkhātatarā ca. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an7.70:4.11"
msgid "Seyyathāpi nāma puriso suvaṇṇanikkhaṃ adhigaccheyya parisuddhaṃ pariyodātaṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an7.70:4.12"
msgid "Tassa evamassa—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an7.70:4.13"
msgid "ayaṃ kho me suvaṇṇanikkho parisuddho pariyodāto, yannūnāhaṃ imaṃ suvaṇṇanikkhaṃ gantvā kammārānaṃ dasseyyaṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an7.70:4.14"
msgid "Evaṃ me ayaṃ suvaṇṇanikkho sakammāragato parisuddho ceva bhavissati parisuddhasaṅkhātataro ca. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an7.70:4.15"
msgid "Evamevaṃ me ime dhammā parisuddhā pariyodātā, yannūnāhaṃ ime dhamme gantvā bhagavato āroceyyaṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an7.70:4.16"
msgid "Evaṃ me ime dhammā parisuddhā ceva bhavissanti parisuddhasaṅkhātatarā cā’”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an7.70:5.1"
msgid "“Sādhu sādhu, sāriputta. "
msgstr "“Good, good, Sāriputta! "

msgctxt "an7.70:5.2"
msgid "Satthāraṃ kho, sāriputta, bhikkhu sakkatvā garuṃ katvā upanissāya viharanto akusalaṃ pajaheyya, kusalaṃ bhāveyya. "
msgstr "A mendicant should honor and respect and rely on the Teacher, to give up the unskillful and develop the skillful. "

msgctxt "an7.70:5.3"
msgid "Dhammaṃ kho, sāriputta, bhikkhu sakkatvā garuṃ katvā upanissāya viharanto akusalaṃ pajaheyya, kusalaṃ bhāveyya. "
msgstr "A mendicant should honor and respect and rely on the teaching … "

msgctxt "an7.70:5.4"
msgid "Saṅghaṃ kho … pe … "
msgstr "the Saṅgha … "

msgctxt "an7.70:5.5"
msgid "sikkhaṃ kho … "
msgstr "the training … "

msgctxt "an7.70:5.6"
msgid "samādhiṃ kho … "
msgstr "immersion … "

msgctxt "an7.70:5.7"
msgid "appamādaṃ kho … "
msgstr "diligence … "

msgctxt "an7.70:5.8"
msgid "paṭisanthāraṃ kho, sāriputta, bhikkhu sakkatvā garuṃ katvā upanissāya viharanto akusalaṃ pajaheyya, kusalaṃ bhāveyyā”ti. "
msgstr "A mendicant should honor and respect and rely on hospitality, to give up the unskillful and develop the skillful.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "an7.70:6.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā sāriputto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When he said this, Venerable Sāriputta said to the Buddha: "

# NOTE: It’s unusual, if not unique for a monk to interpret the “Buddha’s” statement, whien in fact it was their own.
#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an7.70:6.2"
msgid "“imassa kho ahaṃ, bhante, bhagavatā saṅkhittena bhāsitassa evaṃ vitthārena atthaṃ ājānāmi. "
msgstr "“Sir, this is how I understand the detailed meaning of the Buddha’s brief statement. "

msgctxt "an7.70:6.3"
msgid "So vata, bhante, bhikkhu satthari agāravo dhamme sagāravo bhavissatīti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati. "
msgstr "It’s quite impossible for a mendicant who doesn’t respect the Teacher to respect the teaching. "

msgctxt "an7.70:6.4"
msgid "Yo so, bhante, bhikkhu satthari agāravo dhammepi so agāravo. (1–2.) "
msgstr "A mendicant who disrespects the Teacher disrespects the teaching. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "an7.70:7.1"
msgid "So vata, bhante, bhikkhu satthari agāravo dhamme agāravo saṅghe sagāravo bhavissatīti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati. "
msgstr "It’s quite impossible for a mendicant who doesn’t respect the Teacher and the teaching to respect the Saṅgha. "

msgctxt "an7.70:7.2"
msgid "Yo so, bhante, bhikkhu satthari agāravo dhamme agāravo saṅghepi so agāravo. (3) "
msgstr "A mendicant who disrespects the Teacher and the teaching disrespects the Saṅgha. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "an7.70:8.1"
msgid "So vata, bhante, bhikkhu satthari agāravo dhamme agāravo saṅghe agāravo sikkhāya sagāravo bhavissatīti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati. "
msgstr "It’s quite impossible for a mendicant who doesn’t respect the Teacher, the teaching, and the Saṅgha to respect the training. "

msgctxt "an7.70:8.2"
msgid "Yo so, bhante, bhikkhu satthari agāravo dhamme agāravo saṅghe agāravo sikkhāyapi so agāravo. (4) "
msgstr "A mendicant who disrespects the Teacher, the teaching, and the Saṅgha disrespects the training. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "an7.70:9.1"
msgid "So vata, bhante, bhikkhu satthari agāravo dhamme agāravo saṅghe agāravo sikkhāya agāravo samādhismiṃ sagāravo bhavissatīti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati. "
msgstr "It’s quite impossible for a mendicant who doesn’t respect the Teacher, the teaching, the Saṅgha, and the training to respect immersion. "

msgctxt "an7.70:9.2"
msgid "Yo so, bhante, bhikkhu satthari agāravo dhamme agāravo saṅghe agāravo sikkhāya agāravo samādhismimpi so agāravo. (5) "
msgstr "A mendicant who disrespects the Teacher, the teaching, the Saṅgha, and the training disrespects immersion. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.123, sc10
msgctxt "an7.70:10.1"
msgid "So vata, bhante, bhikkhu satthari agāravo dhamme agāravo saṅghe agāravo sikkhāya agāravo samādhismiṃ agāravo appamāde sagāravo bhavissatīti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati. "
msgstr "It’s quite impossible for a mendicant who doesn’t respect the Teacher, the teaching, the Saṅgha, the training, and immersion to respect diligence. "

msgctxt "an7.70:10.2"
msgid "Yo so, bhante, bhikkhu satthari agāravo dhamme agāravo saṅghe agāravo sikkhāya agāravo samādhismiṃ agāravo appamādepi so agāravo. (6) "
msgstr "A mendicant who disrespects the Teacher, the teaching, the Saṅgha, the training, and immersion disrespects diligence. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc11
msgctxt "an7.70:11.1"
msgid "So vata, bhante, bhikkhu satthari agāravo dhamme agāravo saṅghe agāravo sikkhāya agāravo samādhismiṃ agāravo appamāde agāravo paṭisanthāre sagāravo bhavissatīti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati. "
msgstr "It’s quite impossible for a mendicant who doesn’t respect the Teacher, the teaching, the Saṅgha, the training, immersion, and diligence to respect hospitality. "

msgctxt "an7.70:11.2"
msgid "Yo so, bhante, bhikkhu satthari agāravo … pe … appamāde agāravo paṭisanthārepi so agāravo. (7) "
msgstr "A mendicant who disrespects the Teacher, the teaching, the Saṅgha, the training, immersion, and diligence disrespects hospitality. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "an7.70:12.1"
msgid "So vata, bhante, bhikkhu satthari sagāravo dhamme agāravo bhavissatīti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati. Yo so, bhante, bhikkhu satthari sagāravo dhammepi so sagāravo … pe …. (1–6.) "
msgstr "It’s quite impossible for a mendicant who does respect the Teacher to disrespect the teaching. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.124, sc13
msgctxt "an7.70:13.1"
msgid "So vata, bhante, bhikkhu satthari sagāravo … pe … appamāde sagāravo paṭisanthāre agāravo bhavissatīti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an7.70:13.2"
msgid "Yo so, bhante, bhikkhu satthari sagāravo … pe … appamāde sagāravo paṭisanthārepi so sagāravo. (7) "
msgstr "A mendicant who respects the Teacher, the teaching, the Saṅgha, the training, immersion, and diligence respects hospitality. "

# NOTE: This is one of those suttas whose elaborate repetitions overweigh the content to the extent that it becomes hard to discern the original pattern. The PTS edition, followed by BB, omits the “positive” turn of the cycle.
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc14
msgctxt "an7.70:14.1"
msgid "So vata, bhante, bhikkhu satthari sagāravo dhammepi sagāravo bhavissatīti ṭhānametaṃ vijjati. Yo so, bhante, bhikkhu satthari sagāravo dhammepi so sagāravo … pe …. (1–6.) "
msgstr "It’s quite possible for a mendicant who respects the Teacher to respect teaching. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc15
msgctxt "an7.70:15.1"
msgid "So vata, bhante, bhikkhu satthari sagāravo … pe … appamāde sagāravo paṭisanthārepi sagāravo bhavissatīti ṭhānametaṃ vijjati. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an7.70:15.2"
msgid "Yo so, bhante, bhikkhu satthari sagāravo dhamme sagāravo saṅghe sagāravo sikkhāya sagāravo samādhismiṃ sagāravo appamāde sagāravo paṭisanthārepi so sagāravoti. (7) "
msgstr "A mendicant who respects the Teacher, the teaching, the Saṅgha, the training, immersion, and diligence respects hospitality. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc16
msgctxt "an7.70:16.1"
msgid "Imassa kho ahaṃ, bhante, bhagavatā saṅkhittena bhāsitassa evaṃ vitthārena atthaṃ ājānāmī”ti. "
msgstr "That’s how I understand the detailed meaning of the Buddha’s brief statement.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc17
msgctxt "an7.70:17.1"
msgid "“Sādhu sādhu, sāriputta. "
msgstr "“Good, good, Sāriputta! "

msgctxt "an7.70:17.2"
msgid "Sādhu kho tvaṃ, sāriputta, imassa mayā saṅkhittena bhāsitassa evaṃ vitthārena atthaṃ ājānāsi. "
msgstr "It’s good that you understand the detailed meaning of what I’ve said in brief like this. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an7.70:17.3"
msgid "So vata, sāriputta, bhikkhu satthari agāravo dhamme sagāravo bhavissatīti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati … pe … "
msgstr "It’s quite impossible for a mendicant who doesn’t respect the Teacher to respect the teaching. … "

msgctxt "an7.70:17.4"
msgid "yo so, sāriputta, bhikkhu satthari agāravo dhamme agāravo saṅghe agāravo sikkhāya agāravo samādhismiṃ agāravo appamādepi so agāravo. (1–6.) "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc18
msgctxt "an7.70:18.1"
msgid "So vata, sāriputta, bhikkhu satthari agāravo dhamme agāravo saṅghe agāravo sikkhāya agāravo samādhismiṃ agāravo appamāde agāravo paṭisanthāre sagāravo bhavissatīti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an7.70:18.2"
msgid "Yo so, sāriputta, bhikkhu satthari agāravo dhamme agāravo saṅghe agāravo sikkhāya agāravo samādhismiṃ agāravo appamāde agāravo paṭisanthārepi so agāravo. (7) "
msgstr "A mendicant who disrespects the Teacher, the teaching, the Saṅgha, the training, immersion, and diligence disrespects hospitality. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.125, sc19
msgctxt "an7.70:19.1"
msgid "So vata, sāriputta, bhikkhu satthari sagāravo dhamme agāravo bhavissatīti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati … pe … yo so, sāriputta, bhikkhu satthari sagāravo dhammepi so sagāravo … pe …. (1–6.) "
msgstr "It’s quite impossible for a mendicant who does respect the Teacher to disrespect the teaching. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc20
msgctxt "an7.70:20.1"
msgid "So vata, sāriputta, bhikkhu satthari sagāravo dhamme sagāravo … pe … appamāde sagāravo paṭisanthāre agāravo bhavissatīti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an7.70:20.2"
msgid "Yo so, sāriputta, bhikkhu satthari sagāravo … pe … appamāde sagāravo paṭisanthārepi so sagāravo. (7) "
msgstr "A mendicant who respects the Teacher, the teaching, the Saṅgha, the training, immersion, and diligence respects hospitality. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc21
msgctxt "an7.70:21.1"
msgid "So vata, sāriputta, bhikkhu satthari sagāravo dhammepi sagāravo bhavissatīti ṭhānametaṃ vijjati. Yo so, sāriputta, bhikkhu satthari sagāravo dhammepi so sagāravo … pe …. (1–6.) "
msgstr "It’s quite possible for a mendicant who does respect the Teacher to respect the teaching. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc22
msgctxt "an7.70:22.1"
msgid "So vata, sāriputta, bhikkhu satthari sagāravo … pe … appamāde sagāravo paṭisanthārepi so sagāravo bhavissatīti ṭhānametaṃ vijjati. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an7.70:22.2"
msgid "Yo so, sāriputta, bhikkhu satthari sagāravo … pe … appamāde sagāravo paṭisanthārepi so sagāravoti. (7) "
msgstr "A mendicant who respects the Teacher, the teaching, the Saṅgha, the training, immersion, and diligence respects hospitality. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc23
msgctxt "an7.70:23.1"
msgid "Imassa kho, sāriputta, mayā saṅkhittena bhāsitassa evaṃ vitthārena attho daṭṭhabbo”ti. "
msgstr "This is how to understand the detailed meaning of what I said in brief.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an7.70:23.2"
msgid "Chaṭṭhaṃ. "
msgstr ""

